data.text:
About

Orchestra Hall is the home of the acclaimed Minnesota Orchestra, whose artistic leader, Music Director Osmo Vänskä, guides a season encompassing nearly 175 concerts that are heard live by 350,000 individuals. Founded in 1903 as the Minneapolis Symphony Orchestra, the Orchestra is recognized for distinguished performances around the world, award-winning recordings, radio broadcasts and educational programs, and commitment to building the repertoire of the future. Orchestra Hall is also home to pops and jazz series and is a renowned venue for artists of many genres. Visit the Orchestra’s website at minnesotaorchestra.org for concert and ticket information.
